        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 12:14PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1214 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Alpine Village, or 10 miles south of Gardnerville, moving northeast
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gardnerville Ranchos, Alpine Village, Mesa Vista, Indian Creek
Reservoir, Paynesville, and Junction CA 88 And NV 88.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
